Interface BSTreeADT<E extends Comparable<? super E>>

Type Parameters:
E - The type of elements this list holds.
All Superinterfaces:
Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
BSTree
public interface BSTreeADT<E extends Comparable<? super E>> extends Serializable

The BSTreeADT interface is designed to be used as a basis for the BST data structure that will be developed in the CPRG 304 class at SAIT. The implementors of this interface will be required to add all the functionality.

      boolean contains(E entry) throws NullPointerException
      Checks the current tree to see if the element passed in is stored in the tree. If the element is found in the tree the method returns true and if the element is not in the tree the method returns false.
      Parameters:
      entry - the element to find in the tree
      Returns:
      returns boolean true if element is currently in the tree and false if the element is not found in the tree
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if the element being passed in is null

    • postorderIterator

      Iterator<E> postorderIterator()
